content:
A dashboard displays data from each widget's source report. You can control which data is visible based on the running user.

Dashboard Data Visibility Considerations:
A dashboard viewer sees data based on the assigned privileges and access of the dashboard's running user.
A static dashboard displays data using the configured user's privileges.
A dynamic dashboard displays data based on the logged-in user.

Configure Dashboard Data Visibility in Lightning Experience: 
Change the running user to control which data is visible to viewers.

Configure Dashboard Data Visibility in Salesforce Classic:
Specify which data to display in a dashboard by selecting a running user.

Dynamic Dashboards:
Create a dynamic dashboard to provide individualized views of data without configuring separate dashboards and folders.
A dynamic dashboard shows each user only the data that they have access to.
title: Controlling Data Visibility in Salesforce Dashboards
